During the course, students will be introduced to the methods of reading, analysing and comparing religious base texts and specifically to the texts to be analysed. A selection of texts will be read, analysed and compared together, by formulating culture related, existential and religious questions, and writing a series of home works and discussing them together.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To acquire an experience of reading and analysing (the translations of) religious base texts, and to learn to compare them and relate them to the human cultural, existential and religious questions, and to apply simpler hermeneutical and exegetical methods, and relevant literature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student - knows the character of the exegesis of religious base texts and understands their importance; - knows and applies the principles of literary, form and tradition criticism; - formulates culture related, existential and religious questions; - following the latter output compares various religious texts; - draws consequences on the context of the authors of religious texts and compares it with our contemporary context; - finds reference and relevant secondary literature, and formulates with their aid conclusions about the formation, contexts and religious intent of the texts.
